WEBVTT

00:02.503 --> 00:03.504
[glass breaks]

00:22.756 --> 00:25.859
(propellers humming)

00:49.317 --> 00:52.120
(traffic rushing)

00:59.160 --> 01:01.762
(bell chiming)

01:13.241 --> 01:16.043
- No man has seen
God at any time.

01:17.044 --> 01:17.845
John 1:18.

01:19.113 --> 01:21.415
How do you define God?

01:21.449 --> 01:25.052
If you look at Christianity,
Judaism, Islam.

01:26.220 --> 01:29.823
Each group, we all
define God differently.

01:31.024 --> 01:34.495
And our definitions are
based on our culture,

01:35.696 --> 01:40.234
our geography, our experiences.

01:40.434 --> 01:42.636
- [Man] Amen, Brother Eli.

01:46.307 --> 01:49.076
- There's a great comfort
in defining things.

01:49.109 --> 01:50.311
Labeling them.

01:51.345 --> 01:53.614
It gives us a sense of control.

01:53.647 --> 01:55.115
But, if we define something,

01:55.149 --> 01:58.719
aren't we saying that
we understand it?

01:58.752 --> 02:02.590
Aren't we limiting it
with our own perspective?

02:09.530 --> 02:10.864
- I love Jesus.

02:17.805 --> 02:20.208
- Thank you, Brother Trevor.

02:21.975 --> 02:22.776
All right.

02:25.679 --> 02:28.582
As you all know, we
have a little potluck

02:28.616 --> 02:31.719
after the service
down in the, um...

02:31.752 --> 02:32.853
- Fellowship Hall.

02:32.886 --> 02:34.288
- Thank you, Miss Martha.

02:34.322 --> 02:36.123
The Fellowship Hall.

02:38.492 --> 02:42.696
You should all try some of my
wife's Tater Tot casserole.

02:43.797 --> 02:44.598
All right.

02:47.935 --> 02:49.069
Thanks so much for coming.

02:49.102 --> 02:51.672
See you all next Sunday.

02:51.705 --> 02:54.308
(choir singing)

03:08.121 --> 03:11.124
(people chattering)

03:27.241 --> 03:28.242
Oh, Trevor.
How are you doing?

03:28.276 --> 03:29.042
- I've got great news
for you, Preacher.

03:29.076 --> 03:30.378
- Oh, yeah?

03:30.411 --> 03:32.446
- I got the Southern
Baptist Board of Churches

03:32.480 --> 03:35.182
coming down here in two weeks.

03:35.215 --> 03:37.318
- Why would they be
interested in coming down?

03:37.351 --> 03:40.153
- Well, I just happened to
know their head talent scout,

03:40.187 --> 03:42.256
Brother Charles
Bucky. (chuckles)

03:42.290 --> 03:45.426
He and I actually went to
huntin' camp together as kids.

03:45.459 --> 03:47.127
I'm the one who actually
drug him to the nurse

03:47.160 --> 03:49.196
after I shot out his eye.

03:49.229 --> 03:51.832
- Well, my father never
joined the board, so I...

03:51.865 --> 03:54.067
- Your father drew 400.

03:54.101 --> 03:55.369
Manuel Baptist is the church.

03:55.403 --> 03:56.737
- Emmanuel Baptist just
gives out door prizes.

03:56.770 --> 03:58.672
- Well, maybe we should
give something out, too.

03:58.706 --> 04:01.008
- Besides the Word?

04:01.041 --> 04:02.476
- I'm gonna go
welcome the visitor.

04:02.510 --> 04:03.243
- All right.

04:03.277 --> 04:05.279
- Good talking to you.

04:09.883 --> 04:11.585
Hello, brother.

04:11.619 --> 04:15.188
I haven't seen you
in church before.

04:15.222 --> 04:18.225
I'm glad you made
it to the potluck.

04:19.192 --> 04:20.227
Do you want to come over

04:20.260 --> 04:23.196
and meet the rest
of the congregation?

04:24.264 --> 04:25.065
Okay.

04:27.735 --> 04:28.669
You want some time by yourself.

04:28.702 --> 04:30.304
I can respect that.

04:30.338 --> 04:31.271
I just wanted to come over
here and introduce myself.

04:31.305 --> 04:32.573
I'm Brother Eli.

04:32.606 --> 04:35.208
I'm the pastor here
at First Baptist.

04:37.311 --> 04:38.111
Okay.

04:40.247 --> 04:42.716
Well, enjoy your food.

04:42.750 --> 04:45.453
- [Man] I like your hands.

04:45.486 --> 04:46.720
- Excuse me?

04:46.754 --> 04:47.855
- Your hands.

04:49.022 --> 04:50.290
They're pretty.

04:51.425 --> 04:54.795
Like you ain't never
done anything with 'em.

04:54.828 --> 04:59.032
- (laughs) Well, I've
done things with my hands.

04:59.700 --> 05:01.134
- [Man] Like what?

05:01.168 --> 05:02.336
- Well, I do my studies.

05:02.370 --> 05:04.938
I wrote my sermon with my hands.

05:06.340 --> 05:09.009
- Church got any place
for folks to stay?

05:10.444 --> 05:14.748
- Unfortunately, we can't have
people staying in the church

05:14.782 --> 05:16.283
because of insurance reasons.

05:16.316 --> 05:18.986
- You got any place I can stay?

05:25.759 --> 05:26.527
- June.

05:26.560 --> 05:27.628
Oh, um.

05:27.661 --> 05:29.062
This is my wife.

05:29.997 --> 05:31.499
What was your name?

05:33.100 --> 05:33.867
- Daniel.

05:33.901 --> 05:34.668
- Daniel, Daniel.

05:34.702 --> 05:36.269
- Hello.

05:36.303 --> 05:40.374
- Daniel, we have a nice
service on Sunday nights

05:40.408 --> 05:42.910
at six o'clock with
a nice worship band.

05:42.943 --> 05:44.945
You're more than welcome...

05:44.978 --> 05:47.314
It's good to meet you.

05:47.347 --> 05:48.148
All right.

05:49.349 --> 05:50.317
- He might come.

05:50.350 --> 05:52.152
- Yeah, you never know.

05:52.185 --> 05:53.353
- [Preacher] If
you've been born again

05:53.387 --> 05:55.055
and you have the love
of God in your heart,

05:55.088 --> 05:58.492
then you are called
to spread his message.

05:58.526 --> 06:00.060
When I go out soul winning,

06:00.093 --> 06:03.497
I go in assuming that
they are gonna get saved.

06:03.531 --> 06:04.765
Now, you may say, Brother Aaron,

06:04.798 --> 06:06.166
it doesn't always
happen that way.

06:06.199 --> 06:09.570
Like seeds falling
on hard soil some...

06:09.603 --> 06:10.704
And sure, there
are gonna be days

06:10.738 --> 06:12.272
when you're giving it your all.

06:12.305 --> 06:14.475
You're knocking on doors,
you're passing out pamphlets,

06:14.508 --> 06:16.376
you're stopping
people at Walmart.

06:16.410 --> 06:18.345
- Something on your mind?

06:20.013 --> 06:21.314
- No.

06:21.348 --> 06:23.383
- [Aaron On Radio] And
still folks don't get saved.

06:23.417 --> 06:24.718
But, you know what?

06:24.752 --> 06:27.755
We need to expect
that the Word of God

06:27.788 --> 06:29.389
is gonna change people.

06:29.423 --> 06:32.325
We preach with conviction
expecting something to happen.

06:32.359 --> 06:34.762
(gun fires)

06:36.430 --> 06:40.133
- [Eli] Praise the
Lord, that's a biggin.

06:40.167 --> 06:40.968
- Yeah.

06:44.371 --> 06:45.372
Follow me.

06:49.342 --> 06:50.744
Did you freeze up?

06:51.945 --> 06:53.947
Most people do on
the first time out.

06:53.981 --> 06:58.185
- [Eli] No, I had no intention
on shooting anything.

06:59.286 --> 07:02.089
(leaves rustling)

07:05.225 --> 07:07.761
- [Man] Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

07:09.497 --> 07:11.599
- [Trevor] I almost
shot your son.

07:11.632 --> 07:12.766
- That's all right.

07:12.800 --> 07:14.134
I got a spare at home.

07:14.167 --> 07:15.202
- God bless you, brother.

07:15.235 --> 07:16.369
- [Man] Hey, He does.

07:16.403 --> 07:17.871
Every single day.

07:17.905 --> 07:18.706
- Come on.

07:24.478 --> 07:25.278
Oh, yeah.

07:26.379 --> 07:28.482
(grunting)

07:29.650 --> 07:33.386
Best part of huntin'
is the cleanin'.

07:33.420 --> 07:37.424
Most people talk about the
trackin' and the shootin'.

07:38.458 --> 07:40.427
Hangin' with their buddies.

07:40.460 --> 07:41.261
Not me.

07:42.530 --> 07:43.997
No.

07:44.031 --> 07:47.635
For me, huntin' is
something you do with God.

07:49.269 --> 07:50.571
I like the blood.

07:50.604 --> 07:54.474
Not the sight of it as
much as the feel of it.

07:54.508 --> 07:56.009
It feels like life.

07:57.244 --> 07:58.912
Like hot liquid life.

08:00.681 --> 08:02.249
It's exhilarating.

08:02.282 --> 08:05.418
You know, sometimes I get
all dressed up for work

08:05.452 --> 08:07.988
in my suit, and my tie,
my hair all gelled.

08:08.021 --> 08:11.224
And I'll spot some
blood on my forearm,

08:11.258 --> 08:13.861
or under my nails,
or on my chin.

08:13.894 --> 08:18.098
Just between you and me,
I don't clean it off.

08:19.332 --> 08:21.001
Nope, I keep it with me
throughout the workday.

08:21.034 --> 08:23.537
I figure if an employee sees it

08:24.972 --> 08:28.542
maybe it'll make 'em
work a little bit harder.

08:28.576 --> 08:30.678
That blood is life.

08:30.711 --> 08:32.680
People respect, and
even fear a man,

08:32.713 --> 08:34.848
who can grab ahold of life.

08:34.882 --> 08:35.683
Take it.

08:37.350 --> 08:38.151
Take it.

08:51.999 --> 08:55.569
You know, offerings this
week was the lowest it's been

08:55.603 --> 08:59.339
since the first year
this church has existed.

09:00.507 --> 09:02.142
- I'm aware.

09:02.175 --> 09:05.512
- [Trevor] The
congregation's grumbling.

09:06.546 --> 09:08.148
- What do you mean
they're grumbling?

09:08.181 --> 09:11.585
- Some folks, not me, of course,

09:11.619 --> 09:14.287
but some folks are
talking about bringing in

09:14.321 --> 09:17.390
another pastor if
things don't improve.

09:17.424 --> 09:18.325
- That's my father's church.

09:18.358 --> 09:19.492
They can't take it away from me.

09:19.526 --> 09:21.094
- If they voted you out,

09:21.128 --> 09:24.932
there ain't a whole lot
you could do about it.

09:27.935 --> 09:29.937
Look, I am on your side.

09:31.705 --> 09:34.274
I'm the one who got the Southern
Baptist Board of Churches

09:34.307 --> 09:36.109
to come down here.

09:36.143 --> 09:37.477
Come on.

09:37.510 --> 09:39.212
That's exciting, man.

09:42.049 --> 09:43.450
- What do we do?

09:45.552 --> 09:48.656
- (laughs) Okay, okay.

09:50.223 --> 09:53.560
First, I need you to
bring your sermons

09:54.594 --> 09:57.430
down to the congregation
a little more, you know?

09:57.464 --> 09:58.799
People around here
like to feel like

09:58.832 --> 10:00.533
something's happening
in their souls

10:00.567 --> 10:02.803
and sometimes you're just
trying to make a little too much

10:02.836 --> 10:04.504
happen in their brains.

10:04.537 --> 10:07.607
So, let's bring back
some questions, you know?

10:07.641 --> 10:09.609
A call and response.

10:09.643 --> 10:10.644
Who loves Jesus?

10:10.678 --> 10:11.444
Well, I love Jesus.

10:11.478 --> 10:12.813
I love Jesus, too.

10:12.846 --> 10:14.514
I don't know, give 'em
something else to do

10:14.547 --> 10:16.549
besides just sitting there
listening to to you ramble.

10:16.583 --> 10:18.919
- You think I ramble?

10:18.952 --> 10:20.954
I outline my
sermons three times.

10:20.988 --> 10:21.989
- Forget I said that.

10:22.022 --> 10:22.823
I'm sorry.

10:24.692 --> 10:28.628
I told the board that the
week they is coming down,

10:28.662 --> 10:31.832
that that was the week
of our annual revival.

10:31.865 --> 10:33.433
- Our annual revival?

10:33.466 --> 10:36.737
- Yeah, we gotta get the
town behind us, you know?

10:36.770 --> 10:38.772
Singin', dancin', rededicatin'.

10:38.806 --> 10:40.073
That sort of thing.

10:40.107 --> 10:41.408
Get as many people out
as we possibly can.

10:41.441 --> 10:43.844
Put up signs, grill
up hot dogs, potlucks,

10:43.877 --> 10:45.178
whatever we need.

10:45.212 --> 10:47.781
Just make a good
first impression.

10:49.016 --> 10:51.885
I've no doubt that you
can be a good preacher.

10:51.919 --> 10:52.853
It takes time.

10:52.886 --> 10:54.487
Folks know that.

10:54.521 --> 10:57.324
All I'm saying is
now is the time.

10:59.526 --> 11:00.894
- [Aaron On Radio] Some folks,
they're gonna get to Heaven

11:00.928 --> 11:02.963
and get many crowns,
and many rewards.

11:02.996 --> 11:04.397
And other folks
are gonna get saved

11:04.431 --> 11:07.467
by the hairs of their chin.

11:07.500 --> 11:09.436
If God gave us what
we all deserve,

11:09.469 --> 11:11.438
we would all deserve damnation,

11:11.471 --> 11:14.708
but his grace, and his mercy,

11:14.742 --> 11:17.677
allows us believers to
enter the Kingdom of Heaven.

11:17.711 --> 11:20.380
And I'll tell you
this right now.

11:20.413 --> 11:23.583
I would rather be the
biggest loser in Heaven.

11:23.616 --> 11:24.752
Think about this now.

11:24.785 --> 11:26.653
I'd rather be cleaning
the toilets in Heaven

11:26.686 --> 11:30.323
than the guy in
Hell who God thinks,

11:30.357 --> 11:32.525
this fella didn't
know any better,

11:32.559 --> 11:35.763
I'm gonna give him
the least punishment.

11:37.865 --> 11:40.834
- Miss Martha says everyone
at the potluck thought

11:40.868 --> 11:42.836
this was the best
casserole there.

11:42.870 --> 11:44.838
She put a picture of it up.

11:44.872 --> 11:46.840
I swear, that woman.

11:46.874 --> 11:48.075
- It was good.

11:49.943 --> 11:50.710
- I'm sorry, babe.

11:50.744 --> 11:52.012
Mine was so much better.

11:52.045 --> 11:54.714
You know mine was better.

11:54.748 --> 11:56.149
- Yours was top.

11:57.150 --> 11:58.451
- [June] Yeah, mine was top.

11:58.485 --> 11:59.719
- I know.

11:59.753 --> 12:00.653
I had both.

12:01.955 --> 12:02.856
- It is different.

12:02.890 --> 12:05.492
Well, I'm not gonna like it, so.

12:06.960 --> 12:10.097
(tense violin music)

12:14.467 --> 12:17.070
(machine beeps)

13:06.386 --> 13:08.188
- [Eli] Daniel, right?

13:09.389 --> 13:10.523
- I'm hungry.

13:14.227 --> 13:16.229
- [Eli] Want to come in?

13:25.939 --> 13:26.739
- [Woman] Preacher.

13:26.773 --> 13:27.841
- Good morning.

13:27.875 --> 13:28.909
- We have got to pay this bill

13:28.942 --> 13:31.611
or they're gonna
shut off the power.

13:31.644 --> 13:33.013
- God will provide, Miss Martha.

13:33.046 --> 13:36.850
- Well, we need him to provide
in the next seven to 10 days

13:36.884 --> 13:39.819
or we're up poop creek
without a paddle.

13:39.853 --> 13:41.754
- Thank you, Miss Martha.

13:43.290 --> 13:44.091
Daniel.

13:51.831 --> 13:53.901
Just leave the door open.

14:03.376 --> 14:05.078
- You read all these?

14:06.646 --> 14:07.747
- Most of 'em.

14:07.780 --> 14:08.848
Yeah.

14:08.882 --> 14:10.017
- [Daniel] Hmm.

14:12.519 --> 14:14.754
- [Eli] Want to take a seat?

14:14.787 --> 14:16.389
- No, I'm all right.

14:21.294 --> 14:23.897
- I've been thinking about ya.

14:31.071 --> 14:32.472
Lunch is served.

14:33.907 --> 14:34.908
Sit down.

14:47.820 --> 14:49.789
So, where are you from?

14:49.822 --> 14:51.424
- A lot of places.

14:58.331 --> 15:00.333
You're smart, ain't you?

15:01.969 --> 15:03.703
- Well, I went to Harvard.

15:03.736 --> 15:04.537
So, no.

15:06.306 --> 15:08.541
- [Daniel] I'm not dumb.

15:08.575 --> 15:09.342
- [Eli] I know.

15:09.376 --> 15:10.343
That was a joke.

15:10.377 --> 15:12.879
- I know what Harvard is.

15:12.912 --> 15:14.481
It's for smart folks.

15:14.514 --> 15:16.716
- Well, I have met a lot
of dumb, and smart, people.

15:16.749 --> 15:17.951
Even at Harvard.

15:19.886 --> 15:23.656
- I'm not educated,
but I'm smart.

15:23.690 --> 15:24.757
I read Prast.

15:25.993 --> 15:26.793
- Who?

15:29.062 --> 15:29.862
- Prast.

15:31.331 --> 15:34.467
The last guy that
told me I was dumb,

15:35.702 --> 15:38.771
I told him to shut
the fuck up. (laughs)

15:38.805 --> 15:41.841
He told me he was smart
'cause he reads Prast.

15:41.874 --> 15:46.079
So, now I try to go to the
library every week, or so,

15:47.080 --> 15:49.849
and read a little Prast.

15:49.882 --> 15:51.518
He's French, you know?

15:51.551 --> 15:52.986
- I think you might mean...

15:53.020 --> 15:56.356
- You never played football
in the mud, did you?

15:59.792 --> 16:01.661
- No, I have not.

16:01.694 --> 16:03.163
- My mama dropped
me at this orphanage

16:03.196 --> 16:05.932
once for a couple of days.

16:05.965 --> 16:09.536
And it backed up on the
piece of old farmland.

16:09.569 --> 16:12.739
It had this dried out river bed.

16:12.772 --> 16:15.708
But, when it rained, it would
turn into a big old mud pit.

16:15.742 --> 16:19.146
There's nothing harder
than wading through the mud

16:19.179 --> 16:20.480
trying to catch a pass.

16:20.513 --> 16:24.717
Even if it's just a few
feet in front of you.

16:25.818 --> 16:27.920
That's what reading
Prast is like.

16:32.992 --> 16:34.927
- It's Proust, not Prast.

16:35.928 --> 16:36.929
Proust.

16:40.333 --> 16:41.301
- Proust.

16:41.334 --> 16:42.169
- Proust, yeah.

16:42.202 --> 16:43.002
Good.

16:47.274 --> 16:49.076
I got a place for you.

16:50.477 --> 16:51.444
- Yeah?

16:51.478 --> 16:52.279
- Um.

16:54.981 --> 16:55.782
Yeah.

16:58.151 --> 16:58.951
- Why?

17:01.888 --> 17:04.824
- Well, you said
you needed a place.

17:19.606 --> 17:20.673
- This'll do.

17:20.707 --> 17:23.042
(Eli laughs)

17:26.313 --> 17:28.014
This place yours?

17:28.047 --> 17:30.049
- Nah, it's my father's.

17:33.586 --> 17:35.788
He kept it from my mother.

17:37.056 --> 17:40.026
She used to disappear,
then wander back into town

17:40.059 --> 17:43.062
kind of drunk and
broke, you know?

17:45.998 --> 17:50.002
Southern Baptist preachers
can't have alcoholic wives.

17:59.612 --> 18:01.881
What happened to your hand?

18:03.116 --> 18:05.452
- You ever been in a fight?

18:07.154 --> 18:08.054
- Verbally.

18:08.855 --> 18:09.856
Spiritually.

18:14.427 --> 18:16.095
Do you want to clean that?

18:16.129 --> 18:17.397
A bandage?

18:17.430 --> 18:20.167
You can wash your
hands over here.

18:27.840 --> 18:29.909
See where the towels are.

18:34.514 --> 18:35.848
Ah, here we go.

18:40.920 --> 18:42.021
(Daniel grunting)

18:42.054 --> 18:43.055
Ah.

18:43.890 --> 18:44.691
Oh, man.

18:57.470 --> 18:58.271
- I got it, I got it.

18:58.305 --> 18:59.306
- All right.

19:07.013 --> 19:07.814
All right.

19:09.549 --> 19:10.417
Yep, sorry.

19:12.319 --> 19:13.119
Okay.

19:23.196 --> 19:24.197
There you go.

19:24.231 --> 19:24.997
You all right?

19:25.031 --> 19:25.832
- Yeah.

19:27.434 --> 19:29.736
- Let's make your bed, huh?

19:38.611 --> 19:40.813
Mind grabbing that corner?

19:43.450 --> 19:44.251
All right.

19:45.552 --> 19:47.354
Just tuck it in tight.

19:51.123 --> 19:51.924
I got it.

19:55.194 --> 19:58.231
(lighter flicks)

19:58.265 --> 20:01.167
Do you mind not
doing that in here?

20:11.278 --> 20:12.279
All right.

20:13.813 --> 20:16.749
Well, there's a gas station
about a mile down the road

20:16.783 --> 20:18.184
if you need anything.

20:18.217 --> 20:21.988
I'll be back tomorrow
with some food.

20:22.021 --> 20:24.357
Glad this worked out, Daniel.

20:40.273 --> 20:41.874
Have a good night.

20:51.217 --> 20:53.653
(door shuts)

20:53.686 --> 20:56.689
(slow violin music)

21:15.274 --> 21:16.809
What are you doing?

21:19.211 --> 21:21.381
- Come on, put the book down.

21:21.414 --> 21:22.181
- Oh, yeah?

21:22.214 --> 21:23.215
