42:00.586 --> 42:02.320
- No, you're not.

42:02.353 --> 42:03.221
- I'm not sorry.

42:03.254 --> 42:04.055
- I know.

42:07.092 --> 42:08.694
- You do this a lot?

42:10.361 --> 42:11.162
- Never.

42:14.900 --> 42:15.701
Do you?

42:18.804 --> 42:20.138
- Yeah, I have.

42:23.208 --> 42:26.812
I knew the second I saw
you at that potluck.

42:28.580 --> 42:30.181
You had that look.

42:31.282 --> 42:32.283
- What look?

42:33.985 --> 42:34.920
- You know.

42:36.487 --> 42:38.389
It's hard to explain.

42:39.557 --> 42:41.492
It's more of a feeling.

42:42.994 --> 42:45.496
It reminds me of making meth.

42:48.166 --> 42:52.370
- How does it feel like
you're making meth?

42:53.104 --> 42:54.572
- 'Cause it's dangerous.

42:55.540 --> 42:56.742
It feels so hot.

42:57.776 --> 42:59.377
If you cook it too long, man,

42:59.410 --> 43:00.511
it'll just blow up
right in your face.

43:00.545 --> 43:02.681
- [Eli] Do you know
how to make meth?

43:02.714 --> 43:03.649
- Yeah.

43:05.450 --> 43:09.054
- Hey, you're not making
meth here, are you?

43:13.424 --> 43:15.627
You're not making meth here?

43:18.529 --> 43:20.031
Do you know what'll happen to me

43:20.065 --> 43:23.735
if they found out I was
holding a drug dealer here?

43:24.602 --> 43:25.503
- I didn't sell it.

43:25.536 --> 43:27.939
- I'll lose my church, Daniel.

43:27.973 --> 43:30.976
- Oh, if you're so
worried about your church,

43:31.009 --> 43:33.611
what are you doing here
in the first place?

43:33.645 --> 43:34.445
Huh?

43:36.414 --> 43:38.549
- I don't normally do this.

43:39.951 --> 43:43.621
I mean, I have these
feelings, but I normally...

43:45.757 --> 43:48.359
Normally I can stuff 'em down.

43:51.296 --> 43:54.599
I read the Bible daily
and I talk to God.

43:57.669 --> 43:59.370
I ask Him to take it,

44:01.472 --> 44:03.709
to take it away from me, but.

44:05.777 --> 44:08.179
- Did you talk to Him today?

44:09.580 --> 44:10.381
- No.

44:12.650 --> 44:13.451
- Too bad.

44:20.025 --> 44:23.328
- Hey, you cannot
make meth here, okay?

44:25.697 --> 44:26.631
No, don't, don't.

44:26.664 --> 44:27.699
- Okay.

44:27.733 --> 44:28.666
- Hey, you cannot
make meth here.

44:28.700 --> 44:29.667
- Okay.

44:29.701 --> 44:30.468
- Okay?

44:30.501 --> 44:31.803
- Okay.

44:31.837 --> 44:33.638
- Give me that.

44:33.671 --> 44:35.206
I want to try it.

44:36.274 --> 44:37.175
- Careful.

44:37.208 --> 44:38.209
- I'm not gonna be careful.

44:38.243 --> 44:39.644
- It's about done.

44:41.312 --> 44:42.680
Okay, give me that.

44:42.714 --> 44:43.982
- Oh, I don't like it.

44:44.015 --> 44:44.816
- Okay.

44:50.621 --> 44:52.123
- You cannot make meth here.

44:52.157 --> 44:53.524
I'm not kidding you
about that, okay?

44:53.558 --> 44:55.126
- I'm not clear on
what you're saying.

44:55.160 --> 44:56.661
- I mean it, don't.

44:57.763 --> 45:00.565
(choir singing)

45:28.559 --> 45:31.362
(phone vibrating)

45:34.332 --> 45:35.666
- Hey, baby girl.

45:37.869 --> 45:39.104
Oh, no.

45:39.137 --> 45:41.773
Daddy misses you, too.

45:41.807 --> 45:42.740
Absolutely.

45:43.942 --> 45:47.245
I can't wait to hear
what's going on at camp.

45:47.278 --> 45:48.880
Did you kill anything?

45:48.914 --> 45:49.714
Really?

45:50.816 --> 45:52.818
All right, that's my girl.

46:02.727 --> 46:06.164
- Hey, I put some extra
onions on it for you.

46:06.197 --> 46:06.998
- Thanks.

46:25.450 --> 46:26.717
You want an over-under knot?

46:26.751 --> 46:27.986
- Jimmy, this ain't supposed
to take all morning.

46:28.019 --> 46:29.520
- [Jimmy] I know,
but it's broken.

46:29.554 --> 46:31.756
- Just tie it tight like a
cheerleader's grip on her Bible.

46:31.789 --> 46:33.191
Sorry, Preacher.

46:34.192 --> 46:35.793
What do you think?

46:38.029 --> 46:39.764
- Looks great.

46:39.797 --> 46:40.798
- All right.

46:40.832 --> 46:43.001
Well, you have a
good day, Preacher.

46:43.034 --> 46:43.935
You know what?

46:43.969 --> 46:45.203
Let's get it as high as we can.

46:45.236 --> 46:46.804
I want God to see it
from his living room.

46:46.838 --> 46:47.973
- [Jimmy] Higher?

46:48.006 --> 46:49.774
- Yeah, get on up there.

46:49.807 --> 46:53.578
- [Host] Trevor Pickins tells
me about your annual revival.

46:53.611 --> 46:54.946
- It's not really annual.

46:54.980 --> 46:58.316
- Okay, that's just
what Trevor told me.

46:58.349 --> 46:59.750
He told me it was an annual.

46:59.784 --> 47:00.718
- It's the first one.

47:00.751 --> 47:02.720
- Ah. (laughs)

47:02.753 --> 47:06.357
That Trevor, he's a
funny guy, ain't he?

47:06.391 --> 47:07.725
- He really loves the church.

47:07.758 --> 47:09.861
- Yeah, I could tell
you some stories.

47:09.895 --> 47:13.731
They would get us fired,
arrested, and divorced nowadays.

47:13.764 --> 47:16.334
- Yeah, well Trevor's
already divorced.

47:16.367 --> 47:17.168
So.

47:18.669 --> 47:22.507
- On that note, let's hear a
little word from our sponsors.

47:23.374 --> 47:24.876
I ain't a dentist, Reverend.

47:24.910 --> 47:28.113
I can't pull no more
teeth, all right?

47:30.048 --> 47:31.382
And we're back.

47:32.250 --> 47:33.751
I miss your father.

47:33.784 --> 47:34.752
I remember him.

47:34.785 --> 47:36.154
He was a great man.

47:36.187 --> 47:37.555
I used to go to his church,
in fact, when I was a kid.

47:37.588 --> 47:38.990
But, now I'm with Brother Aaron.

47:39.024 --> 47:41.026
- Well, First Baptist isn't
my father's church anymore.

47:41.059 --> 47:42.593
It's mine.

47:42.627 --> 47:46.797
And with this revival, I'm
taking it in a new direction.

47:47.933 --> 47:48.699
- [Host] And what direction
is that, Reverend?

47:48.733 --> 47:49.434
- Forward.

47:50.001 --> 47:51.836
- What exactly does that mean?

47:51.869 --> 47:54.005
- Let me ask you, Jim.

47:54.039 --> 47:56.241
Why'd you leave First Baptist?

47:56.274 --> 47:57.842
- Well, my kids.

47:57.875 --> 48:01.379
My kids, they heard Emmanuel
Baptist was exciting.

48:01.412 --> 48:03.814
And whatever keeps my
kids' interest in the Lord

48:03.848 --> 48:05.483
and off their
phones, am I right?

48:05.516 --> 48:06.284
- No.

48:06.317 --> 48:07.218
No, Jim.

48:07.252 --> 48:08.519
I don't think you are right.

48:08.553 --> 48:11.056
You know, Brother Aaron
might have the cameras,

48:11.089 --> 48:12.857
and the lights, and the
screens, and all that,

48:12.890 --> 48:14.825
but I'm not Brother Aaron.

48:14.859 --> 48:15.726
I am not Brother Aaron.

48:15.760 --> 48:16.827
I will never be Brother Aaron.

48:16.861 --> 48:19.864
I do not want to
be Brother Aaron.

48:19.897 --> 48:22.100
I'm trying to make something
true, something real.

48:22.133 --> 48:24.669
And it's hard being a pastor.

48:26.137 --> 48:26.938
It's hard.

48:28.139 --> 48:30.275
It's hard to be a Christian.

48:30.308 --> 48:31.876
It's hard to know
what God wants.

48:31.909 --> 48:35.913
And when you do know what God
wants, it's hard to do it.

48:36.781 --> 48:37.515
Jim, let me ask you.

48:37.548 --> 48:39.084
Do you ever feel alone?

48:39.117 --> 48:39.884
- Yeah, sure.

48:39.917 --> 48:40.885
- Of course you do.

48:40.918 --> 48:42.853
We all feel alone.

48:42.887 --> 48:44.189
We all feel lost.

48:45.156 --> 48:46.824
We all feel scared.

48:46.857 --> 48:48.559
We all feel darkness.

48:50.661 --> 48:52.964
We get caught up in
the small day-to-day

48:52.998 --> 48:55.400
and we lose sight of eternity.

48:57.502 --> 48:58.269
We make mistakes.

48:58.303 --> 48:59.437
I make mistakes.

48:59.470 --> 49:00.505
I've made so many mistakes.

49:00.538 --> 49:02.240
I'm not perfect.

49:02.273 --> 49:03.941
I'm far from perfect.

49:05.143 --> 49:08.913
But, God's love, and His
grace, and His power,

49:10.615 --> 49:12.950
are bigger than that.

49:12.984 --> 49:17.188
And that's what the revival
is about next weekend.

49:18.389 --> 49:21.859
It's about imperfect
people coming together

49:21.892 --> 49:24.162
to feel the power and love.

49:24.195 --> 49:27.865
And they need the strength
to keep on living.

49:27.898 --> 49:30.201
Who doesn't want that, right?

49:34.339 --> 49:35.206
- [Jim] All right.

49:35.240 --> 49:36.207
That's gonna do it for us.

49:36.241 --> 49:38.543
Remember, two weeks from Sunday.

49:38.576 --> 49:40.911
First Baptist Church Revival.

49:42.580 --> 49:45.150
(slow violin music)

49:45.183 --> 49:48.419
- [Aaron] Woe unto you,
you scribes and Pharisees.

49:48.453 --> 49:49.720
Hypocrites.

49:49.754 --> 49:51.989
For you they're like
whited sepulchers

49:52.023 --> 49:54.159
which indeed appear
beautiful outward,

49:54.192 --> 49:57.962
but are full of dead man's
bones and all uncleanness.

49:57.995 --> 50:01.299
Even so, ye outwardly
appear righteous unto man,

50:01.332 --> 50:04.969
but within you're full of
hypocrisy and inequity.

50:05.002 --> 50:08.306
Woe unto you scribes
and Pharisees.

50:08.339 --> 50:09.907
Hypocrites.

50:09.940 --> 50:13.144
Fill ye up then the measures
of your fathers, you serpents.

50:13.178 --> 50:15.046
You generation of vipers.

50:15.080 --> 50:18.583
How can you escape
the damnation of Hell?

50:58.489 --> 51:00.858
(door closes)

51:00.891 --> 51:02.960
- [Eli] You're up late.

51:02.993 --> 51:04.362
- [June] Where were you?

51:04.395 --> 51:06.697
- [Eli] I was at church.

51:06.731 --> 51:08.833
- Something came for you.

51:40.765 --> 51:43.501
- This is not what
it looks like.

51:48.038 --> 51:49.039
- Well, hey.

51:50.308 --> 51:51.542
Why did you do this?

51:51.576 --> 51:53.878
- Sometimes men embrace.

51:53.911 --> 51:55.946
- Don't lie to me, Eli.

51:55.980 --> 51:57.515
- June, June, June.

52:01.085 --> 52:03.020
I care about you so much.

52:03.053 --> 52:04.255
I love you.

52:04.289 --> 52:05.156
I love you.

52:06.191 --> 52:07.858
I just got confused.

52:07.892 --> 52:12.096
I get happy, but this
thing I know is wrong

52:12.930 --> 52:15.065
and I don't know what I'm doing.

52:15.099 --> 52:17.235
I question things, but.

52:17.268 --> 52:18.703
- I can't do this.

52:18.736 --> 52:20.205
- June, June, June.

52:21.071 --> 52:22.907
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

52:22.940 --> 52:24.074
I'm so sorry.

52:25.343 --> 52:26.777
I've sinned.

52:26.811 --> 52:31.015
I'm a sinner, but I'm
gonna fix it, all right?

52:31.716 --> 52:32.750
I'm gonna fix it.

52:32.783 --> 52:34.051
I'm back.

52:34.084 --> 52:36.321
Trust me, I will fix it.

52:36.354 --> 52:37.555
I will fix it.

52:39.190 --> 52:40.391
I will fix it.

52:50.301 --> 52:53.604
(uptempo violin music)

53:08.553 --> 53:09.420
- [Aaron] Listen, church.

53:09.454 --> 53:10.621
When you go out soul winning,

53:10.655 --> 53:12.189
a lot of you are walking
around, excuse me,

53:12.223 --> 53:14.792
but a lot of you are
walking around like losers.

53:14.825 --> 53:16.227
And, hello.

53:16.261 --> 53:19.330
It's called soul
winning, not soul losing.

53:20.798 --> 53:22.132
You know, you think no
one's gonna listen to you.

53:22.166 --> 53:24.101
Do you think Christ
thought no one was gonna?

53:24.134 --> 53:26.170
I can tell you, He
was not a loser.

53:26.203 --> 53:28.439
You think Christ assumes
folks at your job

53:28.473 --> 53:29.640
aren't gonna get saved?

53:29.674 --> 53:31.976
You think Christ
assumes folks at Walmart

53:32.009 --> 53:33.378
aren't gonna get saved?

53:33.411 --> 53:35.580
I've seen more folks saved
at Walmart than church.

53:35.613 --> 53:37.114
Praise God.

53:37.147 --> 53:38.916
You will be eternally
surprised by who gets saved

53:38.949 --> 53:40.918
and where they get saved.

53:40.951 --> 53:42.186
Look, I do this, too.

53:42.219 --> 53:43.354
I look at a fella
coming out of a bar

53:43.388 --> 53:44.755
and I think that is
the last man on earth

53:44.789 --> 53:45.823
who is gonna get saved.

53:45.856 --> 53:47.024
And guess you what?

53:47.057 --> 53:49.193
There I see him on
Sunday and he got saved

53:49.226 --> 53:51.529
and I start thinking,
what do you guys say?

53:51.562 --> 53:54.399
But, there ain't no way
he's gonna live for God.

53:54.432 --> 53:56.166
I can't really see him
getting into church

53:56.200 --> 53:58.235
or making bigger
changes in his life.

53:58.269 --> 54:01.205
And lo and behold,
God changes people

54:01.238 --> 54:04.642
and the spirit of God has the
power to change the heart.

54:04.675 --> 54:06.210
Listen, church.

54:06.243 --> 54:09.947
When I go out soul winning,
I don't expect to fail.

54:09.980 --> 54:11.582
I expect to succeed.

54:18.122 --> 54:19.790
(door opens)

54:19.824 --> 54:20.591
- Hi.

54:20.625 --> 54:21.692
- Hey.

54:21.726 --> 54:22.493
- How you doing?

54:22.527 --> 54:23.328
- Okay.

54:24.194 --> 54:26.297
- Blessed to see you.

54:26.331 --> 54:27.798
- Yeah.

54:27.832 --> 54:30.100
Brought you something.

54:30.134 --> 54:31.569
- What?

54:31.602 --> 54:34.238
- You don't have to go to the
library every week to read it.

54:34.271 --> 54:36.374
- I don't have anything for you.

54:36.407 --> 54:40.010
- Um, I gotta talk to
you about something.

54:42.279 --> 54:45.149
There's a picture
of us together.

54:49.620 --> 54:50.421
- So what?

54:57.362 --> 54:58.363
No.

54:59.864 --> 55:00.665
No.

55:02.467 --> 55:03.233
Not you.

55:05.235 --> 55:08.038
You said you wanted
to be with me.

55:11.509 --> 55:12.643
Listen to me.

55:15.112 --> 55:17.382
I have real feelings for you.

55:19.884 --> 55:22.186
- And I'm committed to God.

55:25.656 --> 55:26.491
- You're committed to God.

55:26.524 --> 55:27.324
- Yes.

55:30.260 --> 55:32.262
- So, why'd you fuck me?

55:34.365 --> 55:36.367
- What we did was wrong.

55:38.403 --> 55:40.405
It's against God's will.

55:42.272 --> 55:43.273
I'm ashamed.

55:49.313 --> 55:50.147
- You're ashamed?

55:50.180 --> 55:51.782
- [Eli] I'm ashamed.

55:52.817 --> 55:53.751
- Fuck you.

55:56.120 --> 55:56.921
Fuck you.

56:02.192 --> 56:03.894
- You have to go.

56:03.928 --> 56:07.131
- Eli, you want me to stay here.

56:07.164 --> 56:10.167
- Daniel, I will pray for you.

56:10.200 --> 56:14.405
I will pray for you every
day for the rest of my life.

56:24.114 --> 56:27.117
(slow violin music)

56:46.437 --> 56:50.040
We all try to understand
God in human terms.

56:51.241 --> 56:54.545
We personify things to
feel closer to them.

56:54.579 --> 56:58.549
We even put words and intentions
in our father's mouth.

56:58.583 --> 57:01.852
We think that he wants
us to buy a new car,

57:01.886 --> 57:05.222
to get a new house,
to get a new spouse.

57:07.958 --> 57:09.359
Can I get an amen?

57:16.100 --> 57:18.435
And we can read our Bibles.

57:19.904 --> 57:22.339
We can say our prayers.

57:22.372 --> 57:25.476
We can convene with
other Christians.

57:26.977 --> 57:30.214
But, does this give us
the right to say that we,

57:30.247 --> 57:34.318
the tiny and insignificant
creatures that we are,

57:35.520 --> 57:38.823
know what God wants in
any given situation?

57:40.825 --> 57:42.392
- [Trevor] Preacher?

57:42.426 --> 57:43.828
- Yes, Brother Trevor?

57:43.861 --> 57:45.129
- I love Jesus.

57:47.031 --> 57:47.832
- Yes.

57:49.066 --> 57:51.001
Yes, we know you love
Jesus, Brother Trevor.

57:51.035 --> 57:51.836
Thank you.

58:00.010 --> 58:01.512
I guess my point...

58:03.313 --> 58:06.316
What I'm trying to
say, maybe, is...

58:14.559 --> 58:16.761
There's someone who's come

58:17.962 --> 58:20.731
to break down our
perceptions of God.

58:21.932 --> 58:25.435
Someone who wants
to show us his love

58:25.469 --> 58:27.872
and his unimaginable wisdom.

58:30.575 --> 58:32.943
Do you know who that person is?

58:32.977 --> 58:33.744
- Jesus?

58:33.778 --> 58:34.545
- Who?

58:34.579 --> 58:35.412
- Jesus?

58:35.445 --> 58:36.413
- I said who.

58:36.446 --> 58:37.815
- [Jimmy] Jesus.

58:37.848 --> 58:39.416
- Who freed us of our sins?

58:39.449 --> 58:40.350
- Jesus.

58:40.384 --> 58:41.485
- [Eli] Whenever we need him?

58:41.518 --> 58:42.319
- [Trevor And Jimmy] Jesus.

58:42.352 --> 58:43.353
- Lord of Lords.

58:43.387 --> 58:44.154
- [Trevor] Jesus.

58:44.188 --> 58:45.122
- King of kings.

58:45.155 --> 58:45.923
- [Trevor] Jesus.

58:45.956 --> 58:46.924
- I said Jesus.

58:46.957 --> 58:47.725
- [Trevor] Jesus.

58:47.758 --> 58:48.525
- Jesus.

58:48.559 --> 58:49.526
- [Trevor] Jesus.

58:49.560 --> 58:50.327
- Jesus.

58:50.360 --> 58:51.295
- [Trevor] Jesus.

58:51.328 --> 58:52.462
- [All] Jesus!

58:52.496 --> 58:53.430
Jesus!

58:53.463 --> 58:54.464
Jesus!

58:54.498 --> 58:55.332
Jesus!

58:55.365 --> 58:56.433
Jesus!

58:56.466 --> 58:57.568
Jesus!

58:57.602 --> 58:58.402
Jesus!

59:01.338 --> 59:03.073
- May I help you, sir?

59:06.944 --> 59:08.212
- I'm a sinner.

59:11.415 --> 59:12.617
- He's a sinner.

59:13.718 --> 59:15.085
Amen.

59:15.119 --> 59:15.920
Amen.

59:18.222 --> 59:19.990
We're all sinners.

59:20.024 --> 59:23.994
We've all fallen short
of the glory of God.

59:24.028 --> 59:26.964
Go now knowing

59:26.997 --> 59:28.398
God is with you.

59:30.500 --> 59:33.604
That God forgives you
and he gave his only son

59:33.638 --> 59:34.504
to die for you.

59:34.538 --> 59:35.339
- I'm gay.

59:38.142 --> 59:40.745
I was with a man just yesterday.

59:41.646 --> 59:42.546
- All right, okay.

59:42.579 --> 59:44.514
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

59:44.548 --> 59:47.351
Are you sorry for
what you've done?

59:47.384 --> 59:50.187
Are you sorry for
what you've done?

59:50.220 --> 59:52.890
Do you believe Jesus Christ
is the way, the truth,

59:52.923 --> 59:54.625
and the life, and that
no one goes to the Father

59:54.659 --> 59:55.993
except through Him?

59:56.026 --> 59:56.794
- I do.

59:56.827 --> 59:57.728
- You do.

59:57.762 --> 59:59.496
You do.

59:59.529 --> 1:00:01.531
Lord, Lord, Jesus, Father.

1:00:05.636 --> 1:00:07.738
Come into this man's heart.

1:00:09.439 --> 1:00:11.141
Cleanse him from sin.

1:00:12.276 --> 1:00:14.645
Forgive his transgressions.

1:00:14.679 --> 1:00:17.181
Show him your love, your way.

1:00:18.582 --> 1:00:22.519
Help him to go forth a
new man with a new life.

1:00:22.552 --> 1:00:25.990
